In [3]:
def model(train_list, test_list, batch_size=32):
    data, label = L.ImageData(source=test_list, batch_size=batch_size, ntop=2, shuffle=True, transform_param=dict(scale=1./255),
                              include=dict(phase=getattr(caffe_pb2, 'TEST')), is_color=False)
    conv1 = L.Convolution(data, kernel_size=3, stride=1,num_output=16, pad=1,weight_filler=dict(type='xavier'), name='conv1')
    relu1 = L.ReLU(conv1, in_place=True, name='relu1')
    pool1=L.Pooling(relu1, pool=P.Pooling.MAX, kernel_size=2, stride=2, name='pool1')
    conv2=L.Convolution(pool1, kernel_size=3, stride=1,num_output=16, pad=1,weight_filler=dict(type='xavier'), name='conv2')
    relu2=L.ReLU(conv2, in_place=True, name='relu2')
    pool2=L.Pooling(relu2, pool=P.Pooling.MAX, kernel_size=2, stride=2, name='pool2')
    fc4=L.InnerProduct(pool2, num_output=32,weight_filler=dict(type='xavier'), name='fc4')
    relu4=L.ReLU(fc4, in_place=True, name='relu4')
    fc5=L.InnerProduct(relu4, num_output=2,weight_filler=dict(type='xavier'), name='fc5')
    loss = L.SoftmaxWithLoss(fc5, label, name='loss')
    acc = L.Accuracy(fc5, label, name='acc')
    return to_proto(loss, acc)
    
def write_net():
    with open(train_proto, 'w') as f:
        print(model(train_list, test_list,batch_size=64), file=f)

def gen_solver(solver_file,train_net):
    s=proto.caffe_pb2.SolverParameter()
    s.net =train_net
    s.test_interval = int(train_num/64)    #60000/64
    s.test_iter.append(int(test_num/64))  #10000/100
    s.max_iter = int(train_num/64)*100       #10 epochs
    s.base_lr = 0.001    
    s.momentum = 0.9    
    s.weight_decay = 5e-4
    s.lr_policy = 'step'
    s.stepsize=4900         
    s.gamma = 0.1
    s.display = int(train_num/64)        
    s.snapshot = int(train_num/64)
    s.snapshot_prefix =root+'model/model'
    s.type ='SGD'
    s.solver_mode = proto.caffe_pb2.SolverParameter.GPU
    
    with open(solver_file, 'w') as f:
        f.write(str(s))

def training(solver_proto, train_acc, train_loss, test_acc, test_loss):
    solver = caffe.SGDSolver(solver_proto)
    
    # the main solver loop
    for it in range(niter):
        solver.step(1)  # SGD by Caffe
        
        # store the train loss
        train_acc[it] = solver.net.blobs['Accuracy1'].data
        train_loss[it] = solver.net.blobs['SoftmaxWithLoss1'].data
        solver.test_nets[0].forward(start='conv1')
        
        if it % test_interval == 0:
            acc=solver.test_nets[0].blobs['Accuracy1'].data
            loss=solver.test_nets[0].blobs['SoftmaxWithLoss1'].data
            for t in range(5):
                solver.test_nets[0].forward()
                acc=acc+solver.test_nets[0].blobs['Accuracy1'].data
                loss=loss+solver.test_nets[0].blobs['SoftmaxWithLoss1'].data
            print ('Epochs ', it // test_interval +1,' accuracy: {:.5f}'.format(train_acc[it]),
                   'loss: {:.5f}'.format(train_loss[it]), 'testing...', 
                   'accuracy: {:.3f}'.format(acc/6), 'loss: {:.3f}'.format(loss/6))
            test_acc[it // test_interval] = acc/6
            test_loss[it // test_interval] = loss/6

#load the model
net = caffe.Net('deploy.prototxt',
                'model/model_iter_9800.caffemodel',
                caffe.TEST)

# load input and configure preprocessing
transformer = caffe.io.Transformer({'data': net.blobs['data'].data.shape})
print(net.blobs['data'].data.shape)
transformer.set_transpose('data', (2,0,1))
#transformer.set_channel_swap('data', (2,1,0))
transformer.set_raw_scale('data', 255.0)

#note we can change the batch size on-the-fly
#since we classify only one image, we change batch size from 10 to 1
net.blobs['data'].reshape(1,1,40,20)
correct=0
wrong=0
time_list=[]
for infile in glob.glob('new_dataset/test/false_positive/*.jpg'):
    #load the image in the data layer
    im = caffe.io.load_image(infile, color=False)
    #im = caffe.io.load_image('test/golden/757.jpg', color=False)
    net.blobs['data'].data[...] = transformer.preprocess('data', im)
    #print(net.blobs['data'].data)
    #compute
    tstart = time.time()
    out = net.forward()
    tend = time.time()
    
    # other possibility : out = net.forward_all(data=np.asarray([transformer.preprocess('data', im)]))
    print('Cost time: {} s'.format(tend-tstart))
    time_list.append(tend-tstart)
    
    #predicted predicted class
    #print(out['prob'])
    if out['prob'].argmax() == 0:
        correct +=1
        print('0', infile)
        #img = skimage.io.imread(infile, as_grey=True)
        #skimage.io.imshow(img)
        #skimage.io.show()
    else:
        wrong +=1
        print('1', infile)
        #img = skimage.io.imread(infile, as_grey=True)
        #skimage.io.imshow(img)
        #skimage.io.show()
print(correct/(correct+wrong), (correct+wrong))
print("Total cost time: {} s".format(np.sum(time_list)))
